oncrete, named example of mission-critical legacy code that has survived for 60+ years.\"}'),(49,61,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Booch\'s direct assertion from a practitioner with 40+ years of industry observation.\"}'),(50,52,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Primary definition from a field co-creator; anchors the claim that the role is decision-centric.\"}'),(51,45,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"The quote describes precisely the mechanism of layered abstraction and inherited defaults.\"}'),(51,59,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"SAGE to modern cloud is a concrete multi-decade example of successive encoding of prior work.\"}'),(51,62,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"RUP\'s practices becoming standard vocabulary illustrates how prior architecture encodes into defaults.\"}'),(52,45,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Quote explicitly situates AI as the latest in a long sequence of abstraction transitions.\"}'),(52,57,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"The quote frames AI as one more abstraction layer, not a category break â€” supports the continuity claim.\"}'),(53,46,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"The IRS case is the paradigmatic example â€” functioning code with no natural death date.\"}'),(53,61,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"The quote captures the permanence of migration as a corollary of code that outlives its context.\"}'),(54,59,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"SAGE\'s longevity and eventual migration illustrates the external-force driver of migration cycles.\"}'),(54,61,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Expert assertion grounded in direct observation across multiple industry cycles.\"}'),(55,46,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"IRS example directly illustrates the problem â€” business rules inseparable from assembly, rationale gone.\"}'),(55,60,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Linux case shows that rationale lives in individuals â€” its loss triggers drift, exactly the migration problem.\"}'),(56,52,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Definition establishes \\\"significant decisions\\\" as the core; the evolution to economic/systemic decisions follows directly.\"}'),(57,50,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Amazon\'s documented formal methods use is an example of codified architectural knowledge.\"}'),(57,51,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Microsoft\'s driver validation work is another example of institutional architectural knowledge being encoded.\"}'),(58,52,'supporting','{\"strength\": 1, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"This is the verbatim primary definition from the co-creator of UML â€” definitive source.\"}'),(59,49,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Contemporary high-stakes use case demonstrates UML\'s value when the three axes are all high.\"}'),(59,53,'supporting','{\"strength\": 1, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Verbatim UML 1.0 specification language plus direct testimony from co-creator â€” definitive.\"}'),(59,54,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Usage data shows UML retained utility in appropriate contexts, qualifying the decline narrative.\"}'),(60,49,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"JWST exemplifies the high-ceremony, high-risk, high-complexity case where formalism is appropriate.\"}'),(60,50,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Amazon S3 example illustrates how scale can push a system into the high-complexity axis.\"}'),(60,51,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Driver software exemplifies the high-risk axis where formalism justifies its cost.\"}'),(60,55,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Primary expert description from the co-creator, though the framework is conceptual, not quantified.\"}'),(61,56,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Illustrative comparison from expert observation; not a verified statistic but credible directionally.\"}'),(62,45,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"The history of abstraction transitions all required judgment at each level â€” AI is no different.\"}'),(62,57,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Direct assertion from field co-creator explicitly in the context of AI tools.\"}'),(63,47,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Historical context of the method\'s development helps assess the inheritance problem\'s origins.\"}'),(63,58,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 04:18:53.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Self-critical assessment from the method\'s creator is a strong source for identifying the weakness.\"}'),(64,63,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Survey data supports the productivity gap finding but does not directly prove the operating-model framing â€” that is an interpretive argument.\"}'),(64,73,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Expert framing identifies the two failure modes that together constitute the operating model problem.\"}'),(65,67,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Bank case study shows structural intervention producing significant results; supports structural change thesis.\"}'),(65,69,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Role consolidation experiment directly demonstrates that team structure change (not just tools) drives speed improvement.\"}'),(65,72,'supporting','{\"strength\": 4, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Historical analogy is rhetorical, not empirical â€” it illustrates but does not demonstrate the structural change requirement.\"}'),(65,73,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Two failure modes framing supports the claim that tool adoption alone is insufficient â€” structural change is required.\"}'),(66,64,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"The 7x/6x structural differentials provide the mechanism explaining why top performers achieve outsized results.\"}'),(66,65,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Survey finding directly supports the 5â€“6x delivery speed claim for top performers.\"}'),(67,63,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Direct survey data for the 5â€“15% average productivity improvement figure.\"}'),(68,66,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Direct survey finding quantifying the scale of role stagnation.\"}'),(69,64,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Direct survey finding for the 7x/6x differentials in workflow and role adoption.\"}'),(70,69,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Client experiment directly demonstrates the smaller pod model producing more teams with maintained quality.\"}'),(71,73,'supporting','{\"strength\": 4, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Expert framing supports that workflow changes (including planning and spec approach) are a necessary layer; specific spec-driven details are asserted framework-style rather than evidenced.\"}'),(72,73,'supporting','{\"strength\": 4, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Expert framing broadly supports the idea that different task contexts require different approaches, but the specific factory-of-agents vs. iterative loop segmentation is asserted without supporting data.\"}'),(73,68,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Tech company case study demonstrates that tool rollout without change management produced no aggregate improvement; change management intervention turned it around.\"}'),(73,75,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Expert framing explicitly positions change management as continuous operational discipline requiring dozens of simultaneous adjustments.\"}'),(74,70,'supporting','{\"strength\": 2, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Survey finding directly quantifies measurement absence among bottom performers.\"}'),(75,74,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Expert opinion describing the proposed framework. Not yet empirically validated as the definitive approach.\"}'),(76,71,'supporting','{\"strength\": 3, \"evaluated_at\": \"2026-03-04 06:57:30.000000\", \"strength_notes\": \"Research finding cited in the talk, but without full citation. Independently verifiable only with the full reference.\"}');
