LOCK TABLES `reasonings` WRITE;
/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `reasonings` DISABLE KEYS */;
INSERT INTO `reasonings` VALUES (1,'If LLM performance degrades from ~90% at 1,000 tokens to ~50% at 32,000 tokens of context, and larger codebases require proportionally more context to represent dependencies and domain logic, then AI productivity gains must diminish as codebase size increases — the tool becomes less effective precisely where the task becomes harder.',2,5,6,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:00:18'),(2,'If the gross productivity increase is 30—“40% but rework also increases after AI adoption, and rework represents definitionally wasted effort, then the net productivity gain must be substantially lower than the gross figure — approximately half, yielding the observed 15—“20%.',2,1,1,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:00:18'),(3,'If all LLM output is fundamentally hallucination (the mechanism by which these models generate text), and some hallucinations happen to be correct, then trying to eliminate hallucinations is misguided — the productive approach is building workflows that detect and filter incorrect hallucinations rather than preventing the underlying process.',3,11,15,'analogical',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:00:58'),(4,'If every major technological advance from canals to the internet has produced an economic bubble, and AI exhibits the same pattern of speculative excess, then AI must also be a bubble — the only unknowns are timing and magnitude, not whether a correction will occur.',3,10,14,'inductive',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:00:58'),(5,'If LLMs architecturally cannot distinguish between data they process and instructions they should follow, then prompt injection is not a bug to be patched but a property of the current paradigm — no amount of fine-tuning or guardrails can fully eliminate it while the fundamental architecture remains unchanged.',4,16,21,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:01:45'),(6,'If the Lethal Trifecta requires all three conditions simultaneously, then eliminating or isolating any single leg breaks the attack chain — this makes mitigation tractable even though the underlying prompt injection problem is unsolved.',4,17,22,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:01:45'),(7,'If any internet access can serve as an exfiltration channel (via image loads, DNS queries, etc.), and any content not directly from the user is potentially untrusted, then the scope of \"sensitive data\" and \"untrusted content\" is far broader than most practitioners assume — tightening the definition of each leg reveals the trifecta applies to more systems than initially apparent.',4,17,22,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:01:45'),(8,'If agents routinely skip steps, create circular dependencies, and enter analysis loops when given self-orchestration capability, and rule-based workflow engines do not exhibit these failure modes because they follow deterministic rules, then the orchestration function should be separated from the agent function — agents should execute tasks, not decide which tasks to execute.',5,31,37,'inductive',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:02:35'),(9,'If the most consistent failure point in software development is the handoff between requirements, design, and implementation (decisions lost in Slack, reasoning re-litigated), and spec-driven development co-locates specifications with source code in the repository, then SDD addresses the root cause by making decisions persistent, version-controlled, and reviewable rather than ephemeral.',5,29,35,'causal',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:02:35'),(10,'If a single general-purpose agent must handle the full complexity of the development lifecycle simultaneously, but multiple specialized agents each handle a bounded subproblem, then specialization trades one complex problem for multiple simpler problems plus interface management — and interface management is a solved problem in software engineering (APIs, contracts, schemas).',5,29,39,'analogical',NULL,'2026-03-03 04:02:35'),(11,'The matrix reveals that the 15–20% average hides a wide distribution — some task contexts see 30–40% gains while others see near-zero, making the average potentially misleading for any specific team.',2,2,1,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(12,'This single-team case study directly demonstrates the rework phenomenon: total code output rose after AI adoption but rework volume also increased, showing how gross gains overstate net productivity improvement.',2,3,2,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(13,'Provides empirical evidence for one of the five moderating factors (language popularity), demonstrating measurable variation from positive to negative productivity impact along this dimension.',2,4,3,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(14,'Directly quantifies the claim with a structured matrix across 136 teams and 27 companies, showing the full range from 30–40% gains (low-complexity greenfield) to 0–10% (high-complexity brownfield).',2,2,4,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(15,'Directly measures the claim across the language popularity spectrum, showing not just reduced gains but actual negative productivity impact for complex tasks in COBOL, Haskell, and Elixir.',2,4,5,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(16,'Provides a theoretical framework for the codebase-size relationship (context windows, signal-to-noise, dependencies), but the presenter himself characterizes this as illustrative rather than rigorously measured — meaning the claim\'s strength depends on future empirical validation.',2,7,6,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(17,'The study\'s scale and design (private repos, longitudinal, cross-sectional) implicitly demonstrates the methodological gaps in smaller studies that rely on public repos, greenfield tasks, or surveys.',2,1,7,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(18,'Provides empirical evidence that the survey-based methodology used by many AI productivity studies produces unreliable results, supporting the claim that such studies are methodologically flawed.',2,6,7,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(19,'Fowler identifies a specific methodological flaw — failure to distinguish workflow types — that reinforces the broader claim about flawed productivity studies.',3,9,7,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(20,'Directly measures the claim — 30-percentile-point average error, only 1 in 3 within correct quartile. Moderate strength due to small sample size (n=43) limiting generalizability.',2,6,8,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(21,'Provides specific quantitative benchmarks (90% at 1K tokens to 50% at 32K tokens) across multiple models. Moderate strength because this is external research that may not directly map to current enterprise AI tools.',2,5,9,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(22,'Fowler direct observation of workflow differences supports the claim that surveys conflating workflows are flawed, though this is expert opinion without controlled data.',3,9,11,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(23,'Fowler reports that his most productive peers prefer agentic approaches over autocomplete, directly supporting this observation-level claim.',3,9,12,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(24,'Practical recommendation from an experienced practitioner, but no empirical evidence on whether this approach actually yields better outcomes.',3,12,16,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(25,'Theoretical argument drawing an analogy to other engineering disciplines. Conceptually interesting but not empirically grounded.',3,15,17,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(26,'Willison is a recognized authority on LLM security, the framework is specific and actionable, and the attack vector described is technically demonstrated.',3,13,18,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(27,'Schneier\'s expert opinion that no agentic AI system is currently secure against prompt injection corroborates the claim that LLMs dramatically expand attack surface with these architectural properties.',4,16,18,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(28,'The Lethal Trifecta definition by Willison directly supports and refines claim 18 by naming the specific architectural combination that makes attack surfaces catastrophically dangerous, not merely larger.',4,17,18,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(29,'The AgentFlayer attack is a concrete case study validating the claim that the combination of private data access, untrusted content, and external communication makes certain agent architectures fundamentally unsafe.',4,18,18,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(30,'Anecdotal observation from a single practitioner. Widely reported by others but not systematically measured here.',3,14,19,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(31,'The recommendation to never use LLMs for deterministic calculation follows logically from the hallucination framing but is based on expert judgment, not measured data.',3,12,20,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(32,'Willison\'s Lethal Trifecta framework implicitly rests on the premise that prompt injection cannot be eliminated — the trifecta only matters if injection is possible. His inability to recommend a safe browser extension architecture corroborates the claim.',4,17,21,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(33,'The AgentFlayer attack is a concrete, working exploit that demonstrates prompt injection in a realistic agentic workflow, corroborating that the vulnerability exists and is exploitable in practice, not just in theory.',4,18,21,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(34,'The AgentFlayer attack is a worked example that validates the trifecta framework: all three legs (sensitive JWT tokens, attacker-controlled Zendesk ticket, public Jira write access) were simultaneously present and exploited.',4,18,22,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(35,'Willison\'s two scope-defining assertions — any internet access exfiltrates data, any non-user content is potentially untrusted — clarify the breadth of two of the three trifecta legs, reinforcing the framework\'s practical scope.',4,28,22,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(36,'Schneier\'s verbatim statement provides direct authoritative support: \"we have zero agentic AI systems that are secure against these attacks.\" As a recognized security authority, this constitutes strong expert opinion evidence.',4,16,23,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(37,'The AgentFlayer case study demonstrates that at least one realistic attack chain was executable in the published timeframe, corroborating the claim that no system was secure against all such attacks.',4,18,23,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(38,'The steganographic browser attack on two separate LLM-powered browsers shows the vulnerability manifested across multiple independent products, supporting the breadth of the \"no agentic system is secure\" claim.',4,20,23,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(39,'The steganographic attack on two LLM-powered browsers is a concrete case study showing the vector is real and already exploited, moving the claim beyond theoretical concern to demonstrated vulnerability.',4,20,24,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(40,'Willison\'s direct quote — \"I strongly expect that the entire concept of an agentic browser extension is fatally flawed and cannot be built safely\" — is the primary evidence. As the originator of the Lethal Trifecta analysis and a leading practitioner, his expectation carries significant weight.',4,21,24,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(41,'The Playwright MCP counter-example shows that browser-based LLM tooling CAN be made safer by isolating credentials — qualifying the claim that all browser-based architectures are unsafe and pointing to the specific design flaw (authenticated session access) that makes extensions problematic.',4,22,24,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(42,'The Lethal Trifecta definition is the logical foundation for the mitigation strategy — if the trifecta requires all three conditions, removing any one breaks the attack chain. This evidence establishes the causal model the mitigation principle depends on.',4,17,25,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(43,'Microsoft\'s Playwright MCP is a working implementation of this principle: by removing the sensitive data leg (no cookies, no credentials), the product achieves a materially safer posture compared to authenticated browser extensions.',4,22,25,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(44,'Willison\'s scope assertions (any internet access exfiltrates, any non-user content is untrusted) help define which leg is most reducible in a given workflow — knowing the scope of each leg is necessary to act on the mitigation principle.',4,28,25,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(45,'Schneier\'s characterization of the problem as existential and largely unaddressed by vendors motivates why a session-level architectural mitigation is necessary — vendors are not solving this at the platform level.',4,16,26,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(46,'The Principle of Least Privilege is the theoretical foundation for the task decomposition pattern — the evidence establishes the security principle that the recommendation operationalizes.',4,23,26,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(47,'This evidence IS the five-step decomposition pattern. It directly supports the claim by providing the specific implementation and its rationale (least privilege at session level, contains compromise to one stage).',4,24,26,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(48,'The Principle of Least Privilege applied at the container level is still subject to the same logic: if the container itself violates least privilege by having both credentials and untrusted content, isolation buys nothing. The theoretical principle explains the caveat.',4,23,27,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(49,'The five-step task decomposition note explicitly states that container isolation does not prevent the Lethal Trifecta from being triggered inside the container if credentials and untrusted content are present simultaneously — directly corroborating the \"reduces but does not eliminate\" claim.',4,24,27,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(50,'The Claude Code Dev Container reference implementation is a concrete sandboxing example that also illustrates the caveat: it defaults to --dangerously-skip-permissions, showing that even a purpose-built sandbox can be misconfigured in ways that undermine its protection.',4,25,27,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(51,'Willison\'s Lethal Trifecta framework explains WHY vetting matters more — each MCP server integrated into an agentic workflow is a potential injection conduit or exfiltration channel. More integrations multiply the attack surface.',4,17,28,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(52,'The MCP Registry\'s status as a directory rather than a certification illustrates the gap: even an official registry does not provide security vetting, meaning practitioners cannot rely on registries as a vetting shortcut and must apply their own discipline.',4,26,28,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(53,'Schneier\'s characterization of the security problem as existential and largely ignored by vendors reinforces why developer responsibility matters: if platform vendors are not solving the problem, individual developers bear the accountability for how they deploy agents.',4,16,29,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(54,'Kim and Yegge\'s head-chef metaphor is the primary evidence for this claim — it directly asserts the responsibility principle and provides a memorable framing. The context (Vibe Coding, 2025) gives it practitioner credibility.',4,27,29,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(55,'AgentFlayer uses public Jira write access (a legitimate task-related capability) as the exfiltration channel, corroborating that even purpose-appropriate internet access can be weaponized.',4,18,30,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(56,'The image-load exfiltration technique is a concrete, specific exploit that demonstrates the claim: a GET request to a PNG URL with a query parameter is indistinguishable from a legitimate image load but transmits data to an attacker. This validates the claim with a worked example.',4,19,30,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(57,'Willison\'s direct assertion — \"any internet access can exfiltrate data\" — is the expert opinion form of the claim. Combined with the image-load case study, strong and moderate evidence converge on the same conclusion.',4,28,30,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(58,'AgentFlayer specifically targets JWT tokens identifiable by a string prefix in files or context. The attack would be ineffective if credentials were never in files accessible to the LLM, directly validating the recommendation.',4,18,31,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(59,'The image-load exfiltration technique illustrates how an LLM with file-read access and network access can silently read credential files and transmit them — exactly the attack vector the recommendation is designed to prevent.',4,19,31,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(60,'The Principle of Least Privilege provides the theoretical foundation: storing credentials in-memory-only implements least privilege for the sensitive data leg — they are available only when explicitly needed, not persistently accessible.',4,23,31,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(61,'The Lethal Trifecta framework identifies external communication capability as the enabling leg — MCP servers with write/publish access are precisely the mechanism that activates this leg in typical developer workflows.',4,17,32,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(62,'AgentFlayer uses a Jira MCP server\'s public comment write capability as the exfiltration channel — this is a direct, worked demonstration of the claim. The attack would be impossible without an MCP server that can publish to a public channel.',4,18,32,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(63,'Willison\'s assertion that any internet access can exfiltrate data establishes the general principle; MCP write/publish capabilities are a specific and particularly capable instance of internet access that amplifies this risk.',4,28,32,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(64,'Willison\'s Lethal Trifecta analysis establishes why registry status matters — each MCP server is a potential injection conduit. The gap between \"listed in registry\" and \"security-audited\" is consequential given this threat model.',4,17,33,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(65,'This evidence directly documents the MCP Registry\'s current state at the time of publication: it functions as a directory, not a security certification. The evidence IS the claim\'s supporting documentation.',4,26,33,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(66,'Evidence about constraints enabling output quality from a different source; corroborates the pattern but from a different domain context.',4,16,34,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(67,'Production deployment across multiple client engagements is the primary validation that structured conventions are necessary for reliable agentic value — though without quantitative measurement.',5,29,34,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(68,'The two-layer architecture (deterministic orchestration + bounded execution) being the consistent pattern across all successful implementations directly supports the claim that structure is required.',5,31,34,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(69,'The source\'s direct counter to the autonomy narrative — asserting constraints enable reliability — confirms the claim from a practitioner perspective.',5,44,34,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(70,'Artifact frontmatter tracking (draft/in-review/approved/complete) and folder conventions demonstrate the operational mechanics of SDD in practice.',3,14,35,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(71,'The convergent design decision between Spec Kit and Kiro — both separating persistent project context from per-feature specs, both stored in the repo — provides cross-product validation of the SDD pattern, though the comparison lacks citation.',5,33,35,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(72,'Practitioner observation from multiple client engagements that handoff breakdown is the consistent failure point gives this claim credibility, though it remains anecdotal.',5,29,36,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(73,'Observed failure modes (skipped steps, circular dependencies, analysis loops) on larger codebases are specific, concrete behaviors — not hypothetical — providing direct evidence against self-orchestration.',5,32,37,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(74,'The contrast is explicit: observed failure modes in self-orchestrating agents versus the reliable enforcement of rule-based engines is the direct basis for this claim.',5,32,38,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(75,'The specific workflow engine rules (requirements before task generation, architecture before implementation, dependency satisfaction before execution) demonstrate concrete enforcement mechanisms.',5,36,38,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(76,'The claim that this observation lacks quantitative backing means the superiority of rule-based engines is practitioner-reported, not measured.',5,39,38,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(77,'The source acknowledges no quantitative benchmarks exist for this claim, meaning it rests on observed patterns rather than measured comparisons.',5,39,39,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(78,'The explicit microservices analogy frames specialization as the architecturally sound choice — a known pattern applied to agent design.',5,43,39,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(79,'Production use across multiple client engagements grounds the analogy in practice, not just theory.',5,29,40,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(80,'The source makes this comparison explicitly, with the same tradeoff framing — one complex system vs. multiple simpler systems plus interface orchestration cost. Direct evidence for the analogy claim.',5,43,40,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(81,'The two-layer evaluation process (deterministic + critic agent) is a concrete implementation of the principle, described with sufficient detail to validate its application.',3,9,41,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(82,'The specific workflow engine rules enforcing completeness before phase progression directly instantiate the principle of inline evaluation preventing downstream error propagation.',5,37,41,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(83,'Production deployment validates the two-layer approach as a working pattern, not just a design proposal.',5,29,42,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(84,'The two-layer evaluation is described with specific implementation detail — linters, test suites, frontmatter presence, cross-reference resolution in layer one; agentic judgment checks in layer two — providing strong case-study support.',5,37,42,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(85,'The concrete example (async queue assumption surfacing in PR diff) demonstrates the mechanism: assumptions become structured diff items, reviewable and correctable, persisting in version history.',5,34,43,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(86,'The reviewer-correction loop — assumption rejected, agent reworks, correction becomes documented decision retrievable by future agents — demonstrates how institutional memory accumulates over time.',5,35,43,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(87,'The specific example (sync vs. async queue decision logged as structured assumption in PR diff) directly illustrates the recommendation in concrete operational terms.',5,34,44,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(88,'The correction loop — reviewer rejects assumption, agent reworks, correction persists as decision — demonstrates the downstream value of structured logging over freeform notes.',5,35,44,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(89,'The deterministic orchestration + bounded execution architecture being the consistent success pattern is the empirical basis for the claim that structure is the enabling factor.',5,31,45,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(90,'Observed failure modes when agents were given meta-level autonomy provide the direct contrast case — more autonomy produced worse results.',5,32,45,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(91,'The source explicitly positions this as a counter-narrative to autonomy-as-improvement, directly articulating the constraint-over-capability argument.',5,44,45,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(92,'The source provides specific examples (specs/REQ-001-*/, REQ-* prefixes, context/ folder) demonstrating how conventions simultaneously organize for humans and enable machine parsing — direct evidence for the dual-purpose claim.',5,38,46,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(93,'Artifact frontmatter (draft/in-review/approved/complete) is another instance of the same pattern: human-readable status that the workflow engine also uses programmatically.',5,42,46,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(94,'The source explicitly self-reports this limitation in its Gaps and Caveats section, making the caveat direct and high-confidence evidence for the claim about absence of quantitative backing.',5,39,47,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(95,'The acknowledged promotional context (QuantumBlack author prominently featuring QuantumBlack tooling) compounds the lack of quantitative data as a credibility qualifier.',5,40,47,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(96,'The scope limitation (greenfield only) narrows the generalizability of even the practitioner observations that do exist.',5,41,47,'deductive','Migrated from claim_evidence.reasoning','2026-03-03 17:27:16'),(138,'Booch\'s quote is a direct assertion of the claim by the co-creator of UML, who has participated in every major abstraction transition since the late 1970s. His first-person observation constitutes strong inductive evidence: if someone who was there for assembly, Fortran, OOP, distributed systems, and cloud all describes them as a single rising-abstraction arc, the pattern is inductively credible.',6,45,48,'inductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(139,'The IRS Assembly case demonstrates deductively: if a system is still running after 60+ years and has not been replaced, then it falsifies the assumption that legacy code dies naturally. The inference from this single case is deductive — one counterexample refutes the claim that code eventually becomes unused.',6,46,53,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(140,'The business rules baked into IRS assembly code illustrate the causal mechanism: when rationale is encoded in a medium that resists extraction, the cost of migration becomes the cost of reconstruction. The causal chain is: rationale not externalized â†’ rationale fused with implementation â†’ migration requires reconstruction â†’ migration cost is unbounded.',6,46,55,'causal',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(141,'The definition is the claim. Booch\'s formulation is deductive: if significance is measured by cost of change, then architecture is definitionally the set of decisions with the highest change cost. This is a tautological deduction — the definition entails the claim.',6,52,58,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(142,'The specification text is direct evidence via deductive reasoning: if the UML 1.0 spec explicitly says UML is not a programming language and says nothing about code generation, then the historical claim that UML was designed as a thinking tool is validated by its own founding document.',6,53,59,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(143,'The quote employs analogical reasoning: Booch compares AI tools to prior abstraction layers (assembly â†’ Fortran â†’ OOP â†’ AI-generated code). The analogy is structurally valid because each prior transition also prompted fears about displacing developers, and each time the shift raised the abstraction floor rather than eliminating human judgment.',6,57,52,'analogical',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(144,'The compute cost comparison supports the claim abductively: the best explanation for why many modern teams build and throw away without architectural investment is that the cost of doing so has dropped to near-zero. The compute analogy makes that cost collapse visceral and serves as abductive evidence for the behavioral shift.',6,56,61,'abductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(145,'The Linux/Torvalds case supports the claim inductively: if conceptual integrity is so dependent on a single individual that Booch predicts drift upon Torvalds\'s departure, then the principle generalizes — architectural rationale lives in people, and when those people leave, the rationale is lost. This is an inductive inference from a high-profile, observable case.',6,60,55,'inductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(146,'Amazon\'s S3 formal methods use provides causal support: Amazon adopted formal methods because the combination of ultra-high scale (complexity axis), data durability guarantees (risk axis), and large-organization accountability (ceremony axis) all pushed the cost-benefit calculation toward formalism. The case causally validates the three-axis model by showing which axes drove the decision.',6,50,60,'causal',NULL,'2026-03-04 04:20:41'),(147,'The survey showing 5â€“15% average company-level gains despite high individual gains inductively supports the operating model failure hypothesis: if tools were the problem, individual and company gains would correlate. The persistent gap between the two levels points to organizational bottlenecks as the explanatory factor.',7,63,64,'inductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 07:00:14'),(148,'If both tool adoption without workflow change and workflow change without structural role change produce marginal results, then the bottleneck is deductively the operating model rather than the tools themselves â€” the only common factor in marginal outcomes is organizational structure.',7,73,64,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 07:00:14'),(149,'The agile transition provides an analogical case: adopting agile practices without restructuring teams and ceremonies produced marginal results; structural reorganization was required. By analogy, AI adoption without structural reorganization is expected to produce the same pattern.',7,72,65,'analogical',NULL,'2026-03-04 07:00:14'),(150,'The bank case study demonstrates that a structural intervention â€” restructuring sprint sequencing, agent roles, and squad organization â€” produced dramatic results (60x agent consumption, 51% more code merges). This inductively supports the claim that structural change, not tool adoption, drives the results.',7,67,65,'inductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 07:00:14'),(151,'The client experiment directly tests the pod model: smaller, consolidated-role teams from the same headcount produced more teams with maintained quality and speed gains. This is inductive evidence that the structural consolidation model performs as described.',7,69,70,'inductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 07:00:14'),(152,'The tech company case study demonstrates a causal sequence: absence of change management caused adoption failure (dropping usage, no impact improvement); introducing change management practices (coaching, upskilling, measurement) reversed the outcome. The before/after structure supports a causal reading.',7,68,73,'causal',NULL,'2026-03-04 07:00:14'),(153,'If bottom performers are not measuring delivery speed and only 10% measure productivity, then measurement absence is correlated with poor performance. Inductively, failing to measure prevents identifying and correcting gaps â€” organizations that do not measure cannot improve what they do not track.',7,70,74,'inductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 07:00:14'),(154,'Research identifying AI code generation as amplifying technical debt directly supports the claim. If AI generates more code faster but at lower structural quality, accumulated debt deductively increases codebase complexity and creates new bottlenecks that offset productivity gains.',7,71,76,'deductive',NULL,'2026-03-04 07:00:14');
